<SLUG> BC-BKN-SUNS-DRAFT-BULLS-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WITH PROSPECTS LIMITED, SUNS SHIP 16TH PICK TO BULLS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BOB YOUNG  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - After looking over the list of players likely to be
available in the middle of the June 30 NBA draft, the Suns elected
Monday to convey the 16th pick to the Chicago Bulls.
</P>
<P>
   The transaction completes the sign-and-trade deal the Suns
negotiated last summer with the Bulls for center Luc Longley. The
Suns still hold the ninth pick of the first round, which they
obtained from Dallas in a trade for Steve Nash on draft day last
summer.
</P>
<P>
   The Suns now will retain its 2001 first-round pick, which would
have gone to Chicago had the Suns elected to keep the 16th pick
this summer.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're looking at a situation where we have to ask whether the
player we get at 16 is going to be able to beat out the player we
get at No. 9 or Pat Garrity for playing time,'' Suns General
Manager Bryan Colangelo said. ``When we assess the depth of the
draft, the player at 16 is probably going to struggle to find time
with this team.''
</P>
<P>
   Colangelo said the Suns had considered the possibility of using
the pick in combination with the No. 9 pick to move up in the
draft. But they determined that the 16th choice doesn't have much
trade value, and other clubs are in a better position to deal.
</P>
<P>
   ``We don't think it has great value to other teams,'' Colangelo
said. ``And there are two teams, Atlanta with four picks and Utah
with three, which have much more flexibility than we have in terms
of packaging picks. We don't have as much leverage as those teams,
and that's all part of the decision-making process.''
</P>
<P>
   The Suns sent forwards Mark Bryant, Martin Muursepp and Bubba
Wells, along with the conditional first-round pick, to Chicago for
Longley shortly after the NBA lockout ended. Longley had signed a
six-year contract with the Bulls as part of the sign-and-trade
deal. Only Bryant played with the Bulls last season. Muursepp and
Wells were released.
</P>
</TEXT>
