<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Tuesday, May 25, and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   HOWARD-COMPLAINTS (Santa Clarita, Calif.) _ When Santa
Clarita-based Howard and Phil's closed shop this month, it gave
many of its employees no warning and, weeks later, some are filing
complaints with the labor board to get their last month of pay. By
Jason Takenouchi.
</P>
<P>
   VITESSE (Camarillo, Calif.) _ Vitesse Semiconductor Corp. said
it will acquire XaQti Corp. for $65 million in common stock. The
transaction, which will be accounted for as a pooling of interests,
is expected to be completed before the end of July. XaQti makes
``network on a chip'' computer processors. By Ben Sullivan.
</P>
<P>
   LLOYD-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Let the hire beware. Daily News
columnist Ken Lloyd, Ph.D., a specialist in organizational
behavior, answers readers' questions on workplace ethics and
relationships.
</P>
