<P>
   WHITE-COLLAR-VICTIMS (Undated) _ The victims' rights movement,
which two decades ago began demanding recognition and help for
those who have suffered from violent crimes, is now turning its
attention to those injured by white-collar crimes. By Leslie Eaton.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
</P>
<P>
   BRAZIL-MARKETPLACE (Sao Paulo, Brazil) _ When news of pressure
on the Argentine peso started to scroll down the computer screens
on trading floors here last week, traders mainly chuckled, stoking
the historic rivalry between Brazil and its neighbor to the south.
But they're not chuckling anymore. By Simon Romero.
</P>
<P>
   KAPLAN-AD-COLUMN _ The agency responsible for that
much-discussed Clairol Herbal Essences campaign in which women
simulate sexual ecstasy now has some excitement of its own: a new
owner.
</P>
