</P>
<P>
   By sending out posters to libraries across the country, the
Romance Writers of America recently tried to dispel the stereotype
of the typical romance reader. The posters, with the caption ``Look
Who's Reading Romance,'' pictured a Harvard-educated cellular
biologist, a telephone lineman, and a superior court judge, among
others.
</P>
<P>
   ``We wanted to show it wasn't a bunch of lonely women at home
with a lot of cats,'' McEachern said.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (EDITORS: Georgina Gustin is a master's degree candidate at the
