<P>
   1999 CALENDAR OF EVENTS
</P>
<P>
   EDS: THIS PART ONE OF A TWO PART FILE.
</P>
<P>
   Compiled by the Cox Washington Bureau and CoxNet
</P>
<P>
   EDS: Adds Billy Graham crusade in Indianapolis June 3-6.
</P>
<P>
   Here is a 1999 news planning calendar, produced by the Cox
Washington Bureau and CoxNet.
</P>
<P>
   This calendar will move on the Cox wire every Tuesday. If you
have anything to add to it that another paper might be interested
in, please call CoxNet at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   Advance obits: Advance obit pages are available on the Cox
server for the following newsmakers:
</P>
<P>
   National:
</P>
<P>
   Ronald Reagan
</P>
<P>
   Billy Graham
</P>
<P>
   Herman Talmadge
</P>
<P>
   Rosa Parks
</P>
<P>
   International
</P>
<P>
   Boris Yeltsin
</P>
<P>
   Entertainment/Arts
</P>
<P>
   Katharine Hepburn
</P>
<P>
   Bob Hope
</P>
<P>
   Eudora Welty
</P>
<P>
   Milton Berle
</P>
<P>
   Sports
</P>
<P>
   Eddie Mathews
</P>
<P>
   Warren Spahn
</P>
<P>
   Hank Aaron
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY, MAY 30
</P>
<P>
   Indianapolis: Indianapolis 500 is held.
</P>
<P>
   NASCAR race at Charlotte Motor Speedway, Concord, N.C.
</P>
<P>
   MONDAY, MAY 31
</P>
<P>
   Memorial Day
</P>
<P>
   TUESDAY, JUNE 1
</P>
<P>
   Hurricane season begins.
</P>
<P>
   Sometime this summer, third installment of Cox's Millennium
package, 2000 years of Christianity.
</P>
<P>
   WEDNESDAY, JUNE 2
</P>
<P>
   Washington: Opening rounds of annual Scripps-Howard National
Spelling Bee (finals begin June 3).
</P>
<P>
   THURSDAY, JUNE 3
</P>
<P>
   Billy Graham crusades in Indianapolis, possibly his last ever
(thru June 6, Dayton covering)
</P>
<P>
   Beijing: 10th anniversary of Beijing's crackdown on dissidents
in Tiananmen Square.
</P>
<P>
   SATURDAY, JUNE 5
</P>
<P>
   Belmont, N.Y.: Belmont Stakes horse race.
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY, JUNE 6
</P>
<P>
   NASCAR race at Dover Downs International Speedway, Dover, Del.
</P>
<P>
   Washington: National Gallery of Art opens with 45 paintings and
10 color prints of Mary Cassatt, one of the most important women
painters of the 19th century.
</P>
<P>
   MONDAY, JUNE 7
</P>
<P>
   Indonesian parliamentary elections.
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY, JUNE 13
</P>
<P>
   Seoul: International Olympics Committee executive board meets.
Agenda includes selecting site for 2006 Winter Olympics.
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY, JUNE 13
</P>
<P>
   NASCAR race at Michigan Speedway, Brooklyn, Mich.
</P>
<P>
   MONDAY, JUNE 14
</P>
<P>
   Flag Day.
</P>
<P>
   SATURDAY, JUNE 19
</P>
<P>
   Davidson, N.C.: World Juggling Day, a day of local festivals
dedicated to the ancient art of juggling.
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY, JUNE 20
</P>
<P>
   Father's Day
</P>
<P>
   NASCAR race at Pocono Raceway, Long Pond, Penn.
</P>
<P>
   WEDNESDAY, JUNE 23
</P>
<P>
   Washington: Smithsonian Folklife Festival begins on the National
Mall (thru July 4).
</P>
<P>
   Washington: Women's World Cup soccer competition is held.
</P>
<P>
   SATURDAY, JUNE 26
</P>
<P>
   Washington: National Barbecue Championship is held in downtown
D.C.
</P>
<P>
   Raleigh, N.C.: Special Olympics World Summer games begin (thru
July 4).
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY, JUNE 27
</P>
<P>
   NASCAR race at Sears Point Raceway, Sonoma, CA.
</P>
<P>
   WEDNESDAY, JUNE 30
</P>
<P>
   Independent counsel law expires if not extended by congress.
</P>
<P>
   THURSDAY, JULY 1
</P>
<P>
   Orlando: National Education Association holds its annual meeting
(through July 6).
</P>
<P>
   Tentative date for start of five-member Caribbean Community
summit (through July 4).
</P>
<P>
   MONDAY, JULY 3
</P>
<P>
   Tour de France begins (through July 25).
</P>
<P>
   NASCAR race at Daytona International Speedway, Daytona Beach,
Fla.
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY, JULY 4
</P>
<P>
   Independence Day.
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY, JULY 11
</P>
<P>
   NASCAR race at New Hampshire International Speedway, Loudon,
N.H.
</P>
<P>
   MONDAY, JULY 12
</P>
<P>
   Belfast: Focal point for annual marches by pro-British
Protestants in N. Ireland.
</P>
<P>
   WEDNESDAY, JULY 14
</P>
<P>
   Paris: Bastille Day.
</P>
<P>
   SATURDAY, JULY 17
</P>
<P>
   New York: Third anniversary of explosion of a Paris-bound TWA
jet shortly after takeoff from Kennedy International Airport.
</P>
<P>
   TUESDAY, JULY 20
</P>
<P>
   Chicago: Start of Internet World trade show (thru July 22)
</P>
<P>
   FRIDAY, JULY 23
</P>
<P>
   Winnipeg, Manitoba: Pan American Games begin (thru August 8).
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY, JULY 25
</P>
<P>
   Cooperstown, N.Y.: Baseball Hall of Fame inductions.
</P>
<P>
   Houston: National Council of La Raza annual conference (thru
July 28).
</P>
<P>
   NASCAR race at Pocono Raceway, Long Pond, Penn.
</P>
<P>
   MONDAY, JULY 26
</P>
<P>
   Geneva: Third session of Conference on Disarmament begins
(through Sept. 8).
</P>
<P>
   TUESDAY, JULY 27
</P>
<P>
   Atlanta: Third anniversary of Centennial Park bombing during
1996 Atlanta Summer Games.
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY, AUGUST 1
</P>
<P>
   Hiroshima, Japan: Start of ``August in Hiroshima,'' the first
world music festival to be held in Hiroshima City. The city plans
to host it every four years (through August 31).
</P>
