</P>
<P>
   SOUTH CAROLINA STRAND: The rivers are dark, the marshes
mysterious and the gnarled live oaks seem to hold ancient secrets.
The upper coast of South Carolina, with its natural charms, beckons
to the adventure seeker. (Includes 4-column color photo of
Litchfield Plantation, 2-column color photo of a boat traveling
down a river and 3-column color photo of downtown Georgetown, S.C.)
</P>
