   WITH: TRAVEL BRIEFS: Vermont will mark the 75th anniversary of
its state park system this summer with programs on crafts, wildlife
and history.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BOOKS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PAGE INCLUDES THREE COLOR PHOTOS AND ONE B&AMP;W PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   FATHERHOOD: In his new book, Leonard Pitts Jr. recounts the
struggle to cope with his anger toward his father and become a
better parent himself. Interspersed with his memories are stories
of other African-American men facing the same difficulties.
(Includes 3-column color photo of Pitts and a 1-column color photo
of the book jacket.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: PITTS TIPS: Advice on how to be a better father.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: BOOK NEWS: It's something of a relief to pick up the first
four volumes in a new series of books, biographies of 150 pages or
so, well written by people who know. The series is called ``Penguin
Lives,'' and at first glance it might be seen as a kind of
biographical literature for the age of the sound bite.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: REVIEW: CRYPTONOMICON: Neal Stephenson's ``Cryptonomicon''
is filled with technical information about the minutiae of
code-writing and breaking, statistics and probability theory and
encryption within various computer programs. There's a plot mixed
in there, too. (Includes 1-column B&AMP;W photo of author as a child
and a 6-pica color photo of book jacket.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: REVIEW: CLOSE RANGE: If there is any blood left in our
romance with the West, Annie Proulx wrings it dry in her powerful
new collection, ``Close Range: Wyoming Stories.''
</P>
<P>
   WITH: N.Y. TIMES BEST SELLERS LIST
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SCIENCE &AMP; HEALTH &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PAGE INCLUDES THREE COLOR PHOTOS AND ONE COLOR ILLUSTRATION.
</P>
<P>
   HEPATITIS C: Hepatitis C. Is this the disease that should scare
the middle-age bejesus out of baby boomers for their dumb
indiscretions 25 years ago? Or is it a medical panic attack that
will pass like a swine-flu scare? (Includes a 4-column color photo
of a Florida doctor telling a patient he has hepatitis).
</P>
<P>
   WITH: HEPATITIS C FACT BOX: A list of facts about Hepatitis C.
