<P>
   SPYING-POLITICS (Washington) _ A House report saying China
pilfered the nation's most coveted nuclear secrets has become an
instant issue in the presidential campaign. Texas Gov. George W.
Bush, the Republican frontrunner, cites the report in attacking
``the (Clinton) administration's failed policies toward China.''
Aides to Vice President Al Gore, the Democratic frontrunner, say
the spying dates to the late 1970s and insist the administration
has taken steps to plug leaks. We look at how the issue will play
in the race. By ERIC ROSENBERG.
