 &HT;    ``You don't watch a movie because it's 35 millimeters or 70
millimeters,'' Romero says. ``It's the idea of the movie.'' That
was when Romero started to succumb to what Carmack calls
``rock-star stuff'' _ maneuvering for fame instead of working hard
(a charge Romero denies).
 &HT;    As nerves frayed, there wasn't much question about which one
would have to go. Doom was a huge hit not because of its ``plot'' _
something about a marine stationed on a moon base that was so lame
that even people at Id can't recall how it goes _ or even the scary
creatures and artsy backdrops.
 &HT;    The key was Carmack's magnificent software, the ``engines'' _
the underlying operating systems that take full advantage of
