<P>
   Food and dining stories from The N.Y. Times News Service for
Wednesday, May 26:
</P>
<P>
   PERU-CUISINE (New York) _ Outdone by visions of gauchos on the
pampas, outromanced by images of Brazilian beaches and Carnival,
and overwhelmed by the familiar flavors of Mexico and the
Caribbean, Peru seems just an anonymous shade in the pan-Latin
palette that has painted many New York restaurants. But if you look
closer, Peru's is the color that shines brighter than the rest.
Eric Asimov.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   With recipes.
</P>
<P>
   With
</P>
<P>
   PERU-MIAMI (Miami) _ A report from the place where North America
gets its first taste of Latin cuisines. By Jon Nordheimer.
</P>
<P>
   With recipes.
</P>
<P>
   CHEF-GEOMANCY (New York) _ What does a four-star chef do before
making a big decision about his restaurant, his personal life, his
long-range career goals? He jots some hash marks on a piece of
paper, and asks a 42-year-old Frenchman named Jerome Brasset to
tell him what to do. Brasset claims he can divine the future
through these marks using an obscure occult system called geomancy.
The bizarre thing is, many of New York's finest French chefs
believe him. Rick Marin.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   MASTER-CHEF (Undated) _ The column: The debut of Thomas Keller
of the French Laundry, widely considered one of the most innovative
chefs in America.
</P>
<P>
   With recipe.
</P>
<P>
   SIMPLE-COOKING (Undated) _ The column: spicy grilled shrimp,
fast and easy. By Mark Bittman.
</P>
<P>
   With recipe.
</P>
<P>
   And a related story:
</P>
<P>
   BARBEQUE (Undated) _ Slow-cooked barbecue, not grilled but
barbecued. By Steven Raichlen.
</P>
<P>
   With 4 recipes.
</P>
<P>
   CILANTRO (Undated) _ The appeal of cilantro in baby form. By
Marian Burros.
</P>
<P>
   With recipe.
</P>
<P>
   WINE-TALK (Undated) _ A new survey tells what Americans really
drink. By Frank J. Prial.
</P>
<P>
   WINE-TASTINGS (Undated) _ A capsule wine review.
</P>
<P>
   SHIGELLA-EATING-WELL (Undated) _ The column: Shigella found in
parsley. By Marian Burros.
</P>
<P>
   ICECREAM-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ Florence Fabricant Reviews
``The Ultimate Ice Cream.''
</P>
<P>
   With recipe.
</P>
