<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas _ The VCR you programmed ahead of time to
record Dick Clark's New Year's countdown refuses to work. The
microwave fails to defrost a pound of hamburger. And the
programmable thermostat has decided it doesn't matter if the
temperature is plunging to 10 below and there's snow on the ground.
The heater isn't coming on. Welcome to 2000. Forget food shortages,
electrical outages and rioting in the streets. It's the little
things that are more likely to get people down when the Y2K crisis
calls on consumers. By JAN JARVIS and JOHN AUSTIN. Story has moved
in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
