   CHAPMAN-TEXAS AT LARGE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ For 64-year-old Tom B. Saunders IV, work has
never been a distant stranger. As a boy, he worked in the boiling
heat of the Fort Worth Stockyards; the rest of his life, he worked
cattle on his family ranch in Parker County. Cattle have always
been an integral part of his life. His family goes back to the
trail-driving days in Texas, to the establishment of commission
houses in the Fort Worth yards, to today's everyday ranching. Now,
in addition to his other daily chores, Saunders is the historian
for the Fort Worth Herd _ longhorn cattle that signify Fort Worth's
150-year history. By ART CHAPMAN. Story has moved in ``a'' general
news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
