<P>
   UNDATED _ The most common question about those people standing
in line to get tickets for the latest ``Star Wars'' epic is: WHY?
As in, why would anyone put their life on hold to get tickets to a
movie that's showing on a minimum of two screens at half of the
theaters in the country? I'm going to go out on a limb here and
guess that the movie will be around for at least a few weeks. Call
me psychic. By MONICA ANDERSON. Story has moved in ``l'' lifestyle
category. &QL; 
