<HEADLINE>
(HLW)
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the stories that New York Times editors are planning
for the Page 1 of Wednesday, May 27. The N.Y. Times News Service
supervisor is Henry Louis Warnken.
</P>
<P>
   For copy info: (212) 556-1927.
</P>
<P>
   For graphics, map, photo info: (212) 556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; TOP: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Lead story: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO (Brussels) _ NATO ambassadors agree to nearly double
the Kosovo peacekeeping force to around 45,000. By Michael R.
Gordon.
</P>
<P>
   1-column hed.
</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move this story by 8:30 p.m. ET in `i' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Top center: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-COX-REPORT (Washington) _ The House committee headed by
