<P>
   GUNS _ WASHINGTON _ House Republicans say they are ready to
accept most gun curbs included in the Senate bill, but have some
differences, including some that would go even further. Democrats,
while pushing for an early vote, say they accept the Senate's
measure and will not try to strengthen it for fear of killing it.
(Foskett, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   w/GUNSTATS _ It is rapidly becoming the urban legend of crime
stats: 6,000 kids caught bringing guns to school but just 13
criminal prosections by the Clinton administration. The stat has
been cited by numerous political figures who are fighting gun
control. But there's just one problem: the statistic isn't really
accurate. Administration says there's an intentional and incorrect
linkage. Rep. Bob Barr, however, says it still proves that Clinton
is lenient on crime. (Judd, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
