<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, MAY 26
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-EPA-POLLUTE-NYT (moved on Friday, May 14)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, May 14,
about a Federal court ruling on regulations about air pollution
misstated the size of particles covered by standards overturned by
the court and the size covered by a separate set of rules already
in force. The overturned standards governing pollutants so small
that they can travel deep into the lungs set limits for the amount
of fine soot particles _ those 2.5 millionths of a meter (2.5
microns) in diameter or less _in a given volume of air. A different
rule regulates coarser particles, those with a diameter up to 10
microns.
</P>
<P>
   BC-KOSOVO-OIL-NYT (moved on Monday, May 24)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, May 24,
about the continued flow of oil to Yugoslavia, despite NATO's
cutoff efforts, referred incorrectly to the cold war political
status of Bulgaria and Romania, signers of the Danube Convention of
1948 calling for free movement of ships. They were part of the
Soviet bloc, not the Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
   BC-BRITANNIA-BOOKDEAL-NYT (moved on Friday, May 21)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, May 21,
about a deal between the author Simon Schama and Talk Miramax
Books, a division of Talk Media, to publish his next work of
nonfiction, ``Brittania,'' misidentified the television outlet for
a series based on the book. It is the History Channel, not ABC.
</P>
<P>
   BC-PATTERNS-FASHION-NYT (moved on Monday, May 24)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, May 24,
about the American Fashion Awards misstated the name of an actress
who is expected to present one. She is Julianna Margulies, not
Joanna Margolies.
</P>
</TEXT>
