<P>
   (NYT29) DURRES, Albania -- May 25, 1999 -- KOSOVO-ALBANIA, 5-25
-- A child plays near a toppled mushroom-shaped bunker, one of
thousands built in the 1970's as a defense against foreign
invasion. Some of the bunkers are currently being used as
protective barriers around the NATO encampments. The transformation
from communist outpost to a member of the European community of
nations has not been easy for Albania. It remains Europe's poorest
country and has suffered through one crisis after another. (Tyler
Hicks/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
