teachers and school administrators who fail to stop
student-to-student sexual harassment may be violating a federal
anti-bias law known as Title IX. (Alan S. Weiner/New York Times
Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT23) OSUBI, Nigeria -- May 25, 1999 -- NIGERIA-AIRPORT, 5-25
-- J.R. Udodia, Shell Oil's general manager in the western part of
the Niger Delta, near the tarmac of a newly constructed air strip.
Years of experience has taught Udodia that the impossible in
Nigeria, like building an airport, is often possible, so long as
certain illusions are maintained. So this facility is officially
known as an air strip, eliminating the red tape and corruption that
would have come with the Nigerian government's involvement should
they have been involved in its construction. (Norimitsu Onishi/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
