<P>
   (NYT19) BOSTON -- May 25, 1999 -- TRAVEL-LIGHTHOUSES-BOS, 5-25
--- With Boston as a backdrop, the nation's oldest lighthouse,
Boston Light, catches a sunset. Colonial history buffs can take day
cruises this summer out to the lighthouse, which was built in 1716
on Little Brewster Island in the Boston Harbor. The 103-foot
granite tower was blown up by the British in 1776 and rebuilt in
1873. It is the last operating lighthouse in the nation that is
staffed around the clock. (David L. Ryan/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
