distinguish one chef's cooking from another's with esoteric
ingredients like micro greens. Such minuscule leaves are already
becoming old hat, as chefs seek out the unusual micro herb no one
has seen before. And right now, it's this baby, also known as
coriander or Chinese parsley. (Michael Rogol/New York Times Photo)
</P>
