<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PULITZER-NODIVORCE-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Pulitzer, investor husband defuse divorce plan again
 &HT;    By Tim O'Meilia
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ The on-again, off-again marriage of
Roxanne Pulitzer and real estate investor Harald Dude is apparently
on again before it was officially off.
</P>
<P>
   Dude filed for divorce Thursday in Palm Beach County Circuit
Court but Pulitzer won't even be served the official papers.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've reconciled already. We're fast,'' trumpeted the one-time
Palm Beach socialite from her car phone Tuesday. Dude would have
been ex-husband No. 4.
</P>
<P>
   ``We believe that every time we get mad, we file (for
divorce),'' laughed Dude, sitting beside her in the car. ``Then we
kiss and make up.''
</P>
<P>
   It's not the first trip to divorce court for the combative
couple. The last time, in 1996, she filed. She declared she needed
$12,393 a month to live on but had no reliable income.
</P>
<P>
   But they made up then, too, and the petition was withdrawn in
1998.
</P>
<P>
   Pulitzer's 1980s divorce trial from newspaper heir Herbert
``Peter'' Pulitzer _ with tales of cocaine, lesbianism and
debauchery _ launched her career as a writer.
</P>
<P>
   Her first book, the autobiography The Prize Pulitzer, was based
on that marriage. Her last book, published in 1995, was a novel
called The Palm Beach Story.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, Dude's divorce suit is still in the court system.
Said his lawyer, Charles Cohen of Boca Raton: ``I can't discuss
what I've heard from my client.''
</P>
<P>
   Tim O'Meilia writes for the Palm Beach Post, West Palm Beach,
Fla.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
